crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious loader designed to decrypt and execute a secondary payload entirely in memory. It utilizes a custom decryption routine (sub_401d70) to unpack a 72KB payload located at 0x404040 in the .data section. Following decryption, the sample implements a manual PE loader (sub_4015d0, sub_401770, sub_4019e0) that maps the payload into memory via VirtualAlloc, handles relocations (sub_401960), resolves imports via LoadLibraryA/GetProcAddress, and adjusts memory protections using VirtualProtect (sub_401850). This reflective loading technique is a common method for evading static security controls.
